A vast medieval battlefield viewed from above, where three distinct armies clash in dramatic formation—one in blue banners, one in orange, and one in deep purple—their forces swirling together in the center like colliding storm fronts. In the foreground, a lone strategist figure stands on a cliff edge, back to the viewer, overlooking the chaos while holding a glowing orb that projects ghostly images of flowing rivers and interconnected nodes, suggesting a different path entirely. The style is Studio Ghibli-inspired with soft watercolor textures, sweeping clouds in amber and violet hues, rolling green hills, and that distinctive hand-painted warmth. Tiny scattered papers drift across the battlefield like fallen leaves, being swept away by the wind toward the horizon where a luminous, organized city of flowing light streams emerges from the mist.
